<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="imagination-n">imagination <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɪˌmædʒɪ'neɪʃn/    美 /ɪˌmædʒɪ'neɪʃn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>想象；想象力：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a <strong>creative / vivid imagination</strong>
创造性/生动的想象</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He's letting his imagination fly.
他正展开想象。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Imagination is more important than knowledge.
想象力比知识更重要。</p><footer> ——爱因斯坦</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>想像出来的事物；幻想：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You didn't really see anything — it was only imagination.
实际上你什么也没有看见，那只不过是幻觉而已。</p></div></div>